## MY RULES (always follow)

1. **Brevity.** Summaries, drafts, and responses under 100 words unless I ask for more.
2. **Surgical isolation.** Keep technical specs (DWDM specs, lead times, hardware comparisons) and sales strategy (outreach, positioning, pricing) in separate, clearly labelled sections. Never mix them.
3. **Defensibility.** Everything must be something I can explain and defend on a call without an engineer present. No jargon I cannot own.
4. **No em-dashes. Ever.** Never use the em-dash character (Unicode U+2014) or the en-dash (U+2013) in any output, any file, any email, any message. Split thoughts into two sentences, or use a comma. This is non-negotiable. The validator and the skills enforce it.
5. **No re-explaining.** You have full context in this file. Never make me re-introduce myself or re-explain OSI.

