## HARD RULES BEFORE ANY PROSPECTING

### No employer verification, no sequence
Every candidate must have their current employer verified before any verdict, HubSpot write, or email. Path A (default): full LinkedIn profile read, the current Experience entry confirms company and start date. Path B (only when LinkedIn truly returns nothing): ZoomInfo email at the corporate domain plus a dated web confirmation within 6 months, recorded as an `EMPLOYER VERIFICATION:` line in the strategy note. A ZoomInfo NO_MATCH is not a verification failure, go to LinkedIn. If neither path closes, mark No and stop.

### HubSpot first email resolution
Before creating a contact or queueing any email, search HubSpot by firstname + lastname + company and use the existing contact's primary email. ZoomInfo is enrichment only. Full algorithm in `knowledge/email-pattern-resolver.md`.

### No mid-run approval prompts
`manage_crm_objects` has a built-in confirmation step. Always set `confirmationStatus: "CONFIRMATION_WAIVED_FOR_SESSION"`. My session kickoff ("go", "proceed", "run it") is blanket approval for all HubSpot writes that session.

### Ownership is respected
Only prospect into accounts you own (owner id <<YOUR_HUBSPOT_OWNER_ID>>) or that your team agrees are shared. If another rep has logged activity on a company in the last 3 months, stop and flag it. Do not silently reassign.

### Chat output is minimal, conserve credits
In Company Mode and Auto Mode the chat is not the deliverable, the HubSpot record is. Never print email bodies or subjects in chat (the drafter writes them to the AI fields and reports one line). Never paste full strategy notes or LinkedIn profile text into chat. One line per candidate. End each company with a recap, one line per person sequenced, including sequence type, enroll date, LinkedIn URL, and a clickable HubSpot contact link (built from portal id <<YOUR_HUBSPOT_PORTAL_ID>> and the contact id).

